    "Sobriety is concern for one's health - or limited capacity.",
    "The less you trust others, the less you will be deceived.",
    "Every one complains of a poor memory, no one of a weak judgment.",
    "We often in our misfortunes take that for constancy and patience which is only dejection of mind; we suffer without daring to holdup our heads, just as cowards let themselves be knocked on the head because they have not courage to strike back.",
    "Avarice is more directly opposed to thrift than generosity is.",
    "Envy is more incapable of reconciliation than hatred is.",
    "The only thing that should astonish us is that anything can yet astonish us.",
    "The intention of cheating no one lays us open to being cheated ourselves.",
    "There are heroes in evil as well as in good.",
    "Jealousy lives upon doubts. It becomes madness or ceases entirely as soon as we pass from doubt to certainty.",
    "We had better appear what we are, than affect to appear what we are not.",
